Multimodal Longitudinal Mental-Health Dataset (Synthetic)

This dataset simulates a six-timepoint longitudinal mental-health study commonly seen in computational psychiatry, digital phenotyping, and clinical outcomes research.
It contains three coordinated data modalities:

Clinical outcome ratings

Passive sensor behavior data

EMA-style natural language clinical notes

These modalities mirror real-world psychiatric research workflows used within
UChicago BSD Psychiatry, Lyons Lab Precision Analytics, and digital phenotyping studies.

